<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 01 at 5:31PM CDT  by NWS Jackson</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Clarke
County through 615 PM CDT...
At 531 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Stonewall, or 9 miles northwest of Quitman, moving east at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Quitman and Stonewall.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
